## What is not part of the engine

- `MODE.md` — workspace-identity (each workspace writes its own).
- `CLAUDE.md` — harness instructions (per-workspace).
- `provenance/` — session records.
- `applications/` — application briefs and artefacts.
- `engine-feedback/` — operator-mediated observations.
- `open-issues/` — workspace-scope issue tracker.
- `archive/` — superseded versions and retired files. Includes `archive/specifications/constraints-v1.md` (the historical six-properties rationale; superseded at engine-v32; design decisions queryable via `bin/selvedge query` on the decisions substrate).
- `state/selvedge.sqlite` — workspace state, not engine-definition.

## Versioning

The engine version increments when any file in the active set above changes substantively, including a substrate migration. Typo corrections and formatting do not bump. Engine-version increments are recorded in the session's `02-decisions.md`. The 078 D-5 release gate constrains *what kind* of change can ship; it does not exempt qualifying changes from the bump rule. Bug-fix and validator-tightening sessions admitted under the gate (which add migrations like 002) bump the engine version normally.

## Engine-version history

`engine-v1` through `engine-v15` ran for 75 self-development sessions and are preserved in git history. `engine-v16` (session 076) was the trim-restart that reduced the active surface to ~430 non-blank lines. `engine-v17` (session 079) applies the 078 D-7 cut, lands the SQLite substrate, and introduces the `selvedge` CLI as the only writer of structured state. `engine-v18` (session 082) adds migration 002 (closes OI-080-001 by adding T-06 trigger pair on `deliberations` UPDATE/DELETE and tightening T-13 to refuse any change-in-place to a non-NULL `sealed_at`) and ships the `selvedge migrate` runner that activates T-15 enforcement (the runner deferral was named at S079 close per `engine-feedback/inbox/EF-079-002-T15-deferred.md`). `engine-v19` (session 083) introduces the coding review loop in methodology v3 and updates both prompts to invoke it. `engine-v20` (session 084) ships Path A: substrate becomes the only writable surface for session state and specifications; markdown becomes a generated export. Migrations 003 + 004; T-17 through T-21 added; T-15 calibrated marker introduced; `bin/selvedge export` materialises provenance markdown from substrate rows; both prompts rewritten to require CLI-only writes. `engine-v21` (session 087) ships migration 008: widens T-06 to admit `body_canonical_in_substrate` flips on closed-session spec_version rows, with a one-time backfill of the three v2 rows whose decomposition completed in S087 (`engine-manifest v20`, `prompt-application v2`, `prompt-development v2`). The widened trigger continues to refuse content edits on closed-session rows; only the canonicalisation marker is now mutable across sessions. `engine-v22` (session 088) ships migration 009 plus four new CLI submit kinds: substrate-native `issues` table replaces 25 markdown OIs as the canonical dispatch surface, with closed-enum status (open/in_progress/blocked/resolved/superseded), closed-enum priority (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW), dedicated link/note/disposition tables, and an alias-format GLOB trigger preserving the historical OI-NNN[-NNN] form alongside new OI-SNNN-N session-scoped IDs. Backfill subagent migrated 30 issues; markdown files deleted; substrate becomes the single source of truth. `engine-v23` (session 089) ships migration 010 (`issue_work_items` M:N join, `work_items.kind` widening to admit `issue_resolution`, T-24 orphan-on-resolve refusal) plus three new CLI subcommands: `selvedge orient` (single-command orientation packet — live read, markdown default, `--json` flag, hard caps with elision footers); `selvedge schema` (sqlite_master introspection with parsed CHECK enums or `--raw` DDL); `selvedge export --issues` (materialises `open-issues/<alias>.md` from substrate so files remain git-trackable). PROMPT.md and prompts/development.md updated to make `bin/selvedge orient` the first session step. `engine-v24` (session 090) ships the PreToolUse hook (`tools/hooks/refuse-substrate-md.py`) wired in `.claude/settings.json` that refuses Edit/Write/MultiEdit/NotebookEdit on `provenance/**/*.md`, `specifications/*.md`, `prompts/*.md`, and `open-issues/**/*.md` unless `SELVEDGE_EXPORT_CONTEXT=1` is set. Resolves OI-085-002 (HIGH, carried four sessions): markdown is now structurally — not honour-system — non-authoritative for substrate-canonical surfaces. Bash-mediated writes remain outside the hook's scope by design (the matcher would otherwise fire on every Bash invocation); the gap is documented in the hook docstring and tracked under a new OI for a future substrate-driven spec-authoring CLI. The substrate engine-definition (migrations, schema, CLI submit handlers) is unchanged; the bump is harness configuration that now enforces the substrate-canonical guarantee asserted since engine-v20. `engine-v25` (session 091) ships migration 011 plus a one-line addition to `_submit_spec_version`: when `spec_id='engine-manifest'`, the handler now atomically updates `workspace_metadata.current_engine_version` inside the same write transaction. Prior to S091, `workspace_metadata` and `spec_versions` were two sources of truth that drifted across S087-S090 (metadata stuck at engine-v23 while engine-manifest v24 was active, causing S091 to open at the stale value). The handler change is the structural defence; migration 011 backfills the metadata to engine-v24 and seeds the `__cli__` UPDATE capability. Also resolves OI-086-002 as already-satisfied (T-03 in migration 001 is the partial UNIQUE index the OI requested). `engine-v26` (session 094) adds the `submit engine-feedback` handler so authoring follows substrate-only-writes (closes EF-S092-4: prior sessions had to write engine_feedback rows via raw SQL). Also fixes two `bin/selvedge export --issues` UX bugs: dry-run output now uses the key `files_planned` (not `files_written`) and includes a `dry_run: true` flag (closes EF-S092-1, the misleading-key trap), and `--write` now reconciles open↔resolved transitions by deleting on-disk files no longer in the substrate's target set (closes EF-S092-2, the stale-path bug that left two markdowns in `open-issues/` after S092). The session-export path gains the same `dry_run`/`files_planned` shape for consistency. `engine-v27` (session 097) ships migration 013 (`forward_reference_dispositions` table + T-26 facet gate), two new submit handlers (`engine-feedback-disposition`, `forward-reference-disposition`), and `prompt-development` v3 (adds §1.5 self-driving dispatch and §8.5 close-time reflection). Together these close the narrative→substrate linkage gap that EF-S095-1, EF-S096-1, and EF-S096-2 surfaced: forward-references and engine-feedback rows now transition through typed substrate writes; `bin/selvedge orient` shows every undisposed forward-reference with an `FR-S<wno>-<seq>` identifier (no longer windowed to the last three sessions); and the development prompt directs successors running PROMPT.md cold to propose work from orient's queue without operator steering. `engine-v28` (session 098) ships migration 014 (`closes_issue` effect wiring: typed `decision_effects.target_issue_id` column with FK to `issues`; T-17 reissued to admit it; T-27 refuses `closes_issue` effects with NULL `target_issue_id`; T-28 refuses any direct `decision_effects` INSERT bypassing the handler-side dispatch) and migration 015 (calibrated table-recreation widening the `decision_effects` UNIQUE to include `target_issue_id` so multiple closes_issue effects within one decision can coexist; triggers reissued outside the calibrated block per S098 EF-S098-2). The `_submit_decision_v2` handler now dispatches `closes_issue` effects through `_submit_issue_disposition` in the same `write_tx` before the INSERT, transitioning the target issue's status to `resolved` atomically with the decision row. `bin/selvedge export --session` renders closes_issue effect lines as `kind alias — descriptor` so provenance markdown traces decision-to-issue flow without re-querying the substrate. `engine-v29` (session 099) extends `_submit_spec_version` to accept inline `body_md`: the handler validates that `body_path` resolves under `workspace_root` (refusing `..`-traversal escapes via `Path.resolve(strict=False).relative_to(ws)`), computes the body_sha256 from the inline content (refusing on declared-vs-computed mismatch), encodes utf-8 bytes-for-bytes, and writes the file in-process *after* the spec_versions INSERT and the engine-manifest workspace_metadata UPDATE succeed (so a constraint refusal never leaves an orphaned body file). Closes OI-S090-5: spec body authoring is now part of the substrate write transaction, replacing the Bash heredoc bypass that S090–S098 relied on when the PreToolUse hook refused Edit/Write/MultiEdit/NotebookEdit on substrate-canonical markdown. `prompt-development` v4 documents the new authoring path in §6 and the `closes_issue` effect contract in §5. `engine-v30` (session 102) ships migration 016 renaming `objects.citable_alias` → `objects.alias` and `issues.citable_alias` → `issues.alias` via `ALTER TABLE … RENAME COLUMN` (SQLite ≥ 3.25), with the T-22 alias-format trigger reissued so its RAISE message names the new column. The first migration attempt used the calibrated table-recreation dance and tripped FK-constraint-failed at COMMIT because dropping `objects` orphans dozens of referrers within the transaction; switching to RENAME COLUMN is non-destructive and auto-rewrites trigger-body column references (only string literals in RAISE need manual update). Closes OI-S101-1 (LOW): the column was the most-trafficked schema name and the rename removes the `o.citable_alias AS alias` indirection that several read-paths in `cli.py` had already adopted. CLI handlers and tests refactored hard-cut: payload field is now `alias`, not `citable_alias`. `engine-v31` (session 104) ships migrations 017 + 018 plus a new substrate-only submit kind. Migration 017 adds `sessions.kind` (operator-declared at open: coding/spec_only/meta; immutable post-open via T-29 mirroring T-23 slug pattern) and the `review_passes` table (one row per reviewer iteration; outcome ∈ clean/findings/nonconverged with operator-asserted `head_sha` for staleness audit). T-30 refuses close on a coding session unless the latest review_pass is outcome=clean or outcome=nonconverged with halt_issue_id NOT NULL. T-20 narrowed to admit the halt path so unresolved findings can be recorded honestly. Migration 018 grants `__cli__` insert capability on `review_passes`. The new `submit review-pass` handler closes the structural-enforcement gap OI-083-001 named (S083 D-2 introduced the coding review loop in methodology v3 but left enforcement as operator-policed). P-2 (codex/openai) cross-family perspective surfaced the staleness-protection requirement (now embodied as `head_sha`) and the manifest-hash-sealing alternative recorded as forward direction OI-S104-1. Halted-as-status-value deferred to OI-S104-3 because admitting it would require a calibrated rebuild of the heavily-FK'd `sessions` table; halt is currently encoded by the review_pass row's outcome on a `status='closed'` session. Methodology v4 supersedes v3 with the substrate-now-enforces sentence. `engine-v32` (session 109) subtracts `specifications/constraints.md` from the engine-definition file set (per S109 DV-S109-1). The document carried the six-properties LLM-agent rationale written after session 076; every constraint it named is structurally encoded in the substrate triggers and methodology kernel. Design rationale is permanently queryable via `bin/selvedge query` on the decisions substrate. Archive copy at `archive/specifications/constraints-v1.md`. Also backfills the substrate table enumeration in the manifest through migration 018 (closing FR-S107-11/FR-S108-10) and corrects frontmatter version drift carried since engine-v31 shipped without updating the file-body version number. `engine-v33` (session 110) ships migration 019 (`harvested_engine_feedback` ledger) plus a rewrite of `_me_harvest_ef` and `_me_status` to read peer engine_feedback rows substrate-direct via read-only SQLite URI with busy_timeout + query_only PRAGMAs. Per S110 D-1 (deliberation_id=10, P-1 anthropic, P-2 codex/openai cross-family converged on Option 1): capability-based peer schema detection over migration-version gating; per-row idempotency via ledger over --since-session coarse filter; SQLite native busy_timeout over Python retry loops. New structured errors E_PEER_BUSY/E_PEER_OPEN_FAILED/E_PEER_QUERY_FAILED/E_PEER_SCHEMA_UNSUPPORTED categorise transient lock contention vs permanent open/query/schema failures. P-2 caught the EF-S005-7 vs EF-S005-1 alias precision error (per-session ordinals, not absolute feedback_ids). Live harvest against selvedge-disaster-recovery imported all 9 peer engine_feedback rows including EF-S005-1 (cross-session provenance reframe, now EF-S110-7 in self-dev) on first run; second run skipped all 9 via ledger lookup.

