he heavily-FK'd `sessions` table; halt is currently encoded by the review_pass row's outcome on a `status='closed'` session. Methodology v4 supersedes v3 with the substrate-now-enforces sentence. `engine-v32` (session 109) subtracts `specifications/constraints.md` from the engine-definition file set (per S109 DV-S109-1). The document carried the six-properties LLM-agent rationale written after session 076; every constraint it named is structurally encoded in the substrate triggers and methodology kernel. Design rationale is permanently queryable via `bin/selvedge query` on the decisions substrate. Archive copy at `archive/specifications/constraints-v1.md`. Also backfills the substrate table enumeration in the manifest through migration 018 (closing FR-S107-11/FR-S108-10) and corrects frontmatter version drift carried since engine-v31 shipped without updating the file-body version number. `engine-v33` (session 110) ships migration 019 (`harvested_engine_feedback` ledger) plus a rewrite of `_me_harvest_ef` and `_me_status` to read peer engine_feedback rows substrate-direct via read-only SQLite URI with busy_timeout + query_only PRAGMAs. Per S110 D-1 (deliberation_id=10, P-1 anthropic, P-2 codex/openai cross-family converged on Option 1): capability-based peer schema detection over migration-version gating; per-row idempotency via ledger over --since-session coarse filter; SQLite native busy_timeout over Python retry loops. New structured errors E_PEER_BUSY/E_PEER_OPEN_FAILED/E_PEER_QUERY_FAILED/E_PEER_SCHEMA_UNSUPPORTED categorise transient lock contention vs permanent open/query/schema failures. P-2 caught the EF-S005-7 vs EF-S005-1 alias precision error (per-session ordinals, not absolute feedback_ids). Live harvest against selvedge-disaster-recovery imported all 9 peer engine_feedback rows including EF-S005-1 (cross-session provenance reframe, now EF-S110-7 in self-dev) on first run; second run skipped all 9 via ledger lookup.
